cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses deep neural networks and their ability to learn generic and specific features for individual classes, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). The proposed metric for measuring the applicability of learned features to individual classes could also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), as it involves clustering and separating classes.
